Durban - A 39-year-old suspect who allegedly stabbed his stepmom following an argument over household chores is due in court on Tuesday. Police said the suspect handed himself over to the police following the murder of his step-mother at KwaNyavu in Umsunduzi. "It is alleged that on Friday morning the suspect and his step-mother had an argument over household chores. "The suspect allegedly grabbed a knife and fatally stabbed her on the head, chest and body. He is appearing at the Camperdown Magistrate's Court, "  KZN police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele. In a separate incident, a 30-year-old man who allegedly stabbed his ex-girlfriend in the neck because she refused to speak to him is due in court on Tuesday. According to KZN police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele, the man was arrested on Saturday afternoon and charged with murder. "It is alleged that on the same day at about 16:55, the 48-year-old victim and her friends were consuming alcohol at KwaBhontshisi near Wyebank, when the suspect arrived and demanded to speak with her. "It is alleged that the victim refused to speak to the suspect who pulled out a knife and stabbed her on the neck. She was rushed to the hospital where she succumbed to her injuries on arrival." The man is due in the Pinetown Magistrate's Court. Daily News 